-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Zurich Insurance, Next Plc, Dia
-- 
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 02:46AM EDT
-- None



July 30 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Zurich Insurance and Next Plc, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Zurich Insurance <ZURN.VX>: RBC cuts to sector perform from outperform * Dia <DIDA.MC>: Nomura raises to buy from neutral; target to 7.30 euros from 6.50 euros  * Next Plc <NXT.L>: Socgen cuts target price to 6737p from 6820p; rating holdFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes.   * AB Foods <ABF.L>: Nomura raises target price to 2480p from 2400p; rating reduce  * Bankia SA <BKIA.MC>: Nomura raises target price to 0.85 euro from 0.80 euro; rating reduce * CTT <CTT.LS>: Jefferies raises target price to 9.50 euros from 8.75 euros; rating buy  * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: S&P Capital IQ raises to buy from hold * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: S&P Capital IQ cuts target price to 32 euros from 35 euros * Dia <DIDA.MC>: Nomura raises to buy from neutral; target to 7.30 euros from 6.50 euros  * Informa <INF.L>: Nomura cuts target price to 570p from 660p; rating buy * Next Plc <NXT.L>: Socgen cuts target price to 6737p from 6820p; rating hold * Orange SA <ORAN.PA>: Nomura raises target price to 14.50 euros from 14 euros; rating buy  * Orion Oyj <ORNBV.HE>: Jefferies raises target to 25.10 euros from 21.50 euros; rating hold * Pace Plc <PIC.L>: Jefferies cuts target price to 425p from 467p; rating buy  * Zurich Insurance <ZURN.VX>: RBC cuts to sector perform from outperform